#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:124
msgid ""
"Still as the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, create a"
" mount point for the EFI partition on the USB flash drive and mount it:"
msgstr ""
"Toujours en tant qu'utilisateur <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, créez un point de montage pour la "
"partition EFI sur la clé USB et montez-la&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:129
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>mount --mkdir -v -t vfat /dev/sdx1 -o codepage=437,iocharset=iso8859-1 \\\n"
"      /mnt/rescue</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>mount --mkdir -v -t vfat /dev/sdx1 -o codepage=437,iocharset=iso8859-1 \\\n"
"      /mnt/rescue</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:133
msgid "Install GRUB for EFI on the partition:"
msgstr "Installez GRUB pour EFI sur la partition&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:136
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>grub-install --target=x86_64-efi --removable \\\n"
"             --efi-directory=/mnt/rescue --boot-directory=/mnt/rescue</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>grub-install --target=x86_64-efi --removable \\\n"
"             --efi-directory=/mnt/rescue --boot-directory=/mnt/rescue</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:140
msgid "Unmount the partition:"
msgstr "Démontez la partition&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:143
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>umount /mnt/rescue</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>umount /mnt/rescue</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:146
msgid ""
"Now the USB flash drive can be used as an emergency boot disk on any x86-64 "
"UEFI platform.  It will boot the system and show the GRUB shell.  Then you "
"can type commands to boot your operating system from the hard drive.  To "
"learn how to select the boot device, read the manual of your motherboard or "
"laptop."
msgstr ""
"Maintenant vous pouvez utiliser la clé USB comme un disque de démarrage "
"d'urgence sur la plateforme UEFI x86-64. Elle démarrera le système et "
"affichera le shell de GRUB. Ensuite vous pourrez taper des commandes pour "
"démarrer votre système d'exploitation sur votre disque dur. Pour apprendre à"
" choisir le périphérique de démarrage, lisez le manuel de votre carte mère "
"ou de votre ordinateur portable."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:156
msgid "Find or Create the EFI System Partition"
msgstr "Trouver ou créer la partition EFI système"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:159
msgid ""
"On EFI based systems, the bootloaders are installed in a special FAT32 "
"partition called an <emphasis>EFI System Partition</emphasis> (ESP).  If "
"your system supports EFI, and a recent version of some Linux distribution or"
" Windows is pre-installed, it's likely that the ESP has already been "
"created.  As the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, list"
" all the partitions on your hard drive (replace <userinput>sda</userinput> "
"with the device corresponding to the appropriate hard drive):"
msgstr ""
"Sur les systèmes EFI, les chargeurs d'amorçage sont installés dans une "
"partition FAT32 spéciale appelée <emphasis>partition EFI système</emphasis> "
"(ESP). Si votre système prend EFI en charge, et qu'une version récente de "
"Linux ou Windows est pré-installée, il est probable que l'ESP soit déjà "
"créée. En tant qu'utilisateur <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, listez toutes les partitions de votre "
"disque dur (remplacez <userinput>sda</userinput> par le périphérique "
"correspondant au disque dur approprié)&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:169
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>fdisk -l /dev/sda</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>fdisk -l /dev/sda</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:172
msgid ""
"The <quote>Type</quote> column of the ESP should be <literal>EFI "
"System</literal>."
msgstr ""
"La colonne <quote>Type</quote> de l'ESP devrait être <literal>EFI "
"System</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:177
msgid ""
"If the system or the hard drive is new, or it's the first installation of a "
"UEFI-booted OS on the system, the ESP may not exist.  In that case, install "
"<xref linkend='dosfstools'/> first.  Then create a new partition, make a "
"<systemitem class=\"filesystem\">vfat</systemitem> file system on it, and "
"set the partition type to <quote>EFI system</quote>.  See the instructions "
"for the emergency boot device above as a reference."
msgstr ""
"Si le système ou le disque dur est neuf, ou si c'est la première "
"installation d'un système UEFI sur le système, l'ESP n'existe peut-être pas."
" Dans ce cas, installez d'abord <xref linkend='dosfstools'/>. Créez ensuite "
"une nouvelle partition, mettez un système de fichier <systemitem "
"class=\"filesystem\">vfat</systemitem> dessus et indiquez <quote>EFI "
"system</quote> comme type de partition. Voir les instructions sur le "
"périphérique de démarrage d'urgence plus haut pour référence."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><warning><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:188
msgid ""
"Some (old) UEFI implementations may require the ESP to be the first "
"partition on the disk."
msgstr ""
"Certaines (vieilles) implémentations UEFI peuvent demander que l'ESP soit la"
" première partition du disque."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:194
msgid ""
"Now, as the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, create "
"the mount point for the ESP, and mount it (replace "
"<userinput>sda1</userinput> with the device node corresponding to the ESP):"
msgstr ""
"Maintenant, en tant qu'utilisateur <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, créez le point de montage pour l'ESP "
"et montez-la (remplacez <userinput>sda1</userinput> par le nœud de "
"périphérique correspondant à l'ESP)&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:200
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>mount --mkdir -v -t vfat /dev/sda1 -o codepage=437,iocharset=iso8859-1 \\\n"
"      /boot/efi</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>mount --mkdir -v -t vfat /dev/sda1 -o codepage=437,iocharset=iso8859-1 \\\n"
"      /boot/efi</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:204
msgid ""
"If you want to mount the ESP automatically during system boot, as the &root;"
" user, add an entry for the ESP into <filename>/etc/fstab</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"Si vous voulez monter l'ESP automatiquement pendant le démarrage du système,"
" en tant qu'utilisateur &root;, ajoutez une entrée pour l'ESP dans "
"<filename>/etc/fstab</filename>&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:209
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /etc/fstab &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal>/dev/sda1 /boot/efi vfat codepage=437,iocharset=iso8859-1 0 1</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /etc/fstab &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal>/dev/sda1 /boot/efi vfat codepage=437,iocharset=iso8859-1 0 1</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:216
msgid "Minimal Boot Configuration with GRUB and EFI"
msgstr "Configuration de démarrage minimale avec GRUB et EFI"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:219
msgid ""
"On UEFI based systems, GRUB works by installing an EFI application (a "
"special kind of executable) into the ESP.  The EFI firmware will search boot"
" loaders in EFI applications from boot entries recorded in EFI variables, "
"and additionally a hardcoded path <filename>EFI/BOOT/BOOTX64.EFI</filename>."
"  Normally, a boot loader should be installed into a custom path and the "
"path should be recorded in the EFI variables.  The use of the hardcoded path"
" should be avoided if possible.  However, in some cases we have to use the "
"hardcoded path:"
msgstr ""
"Sur les systèmes basés sur UEFI, GRUB fonctionne en installant une "
"application EFI (un type d'exécutable spécial) dans l'ESP. Le micrologiciel "
"EFI recherchera les chargeurs d'amorçage dans les applications EFI à partir "
"des entrées de démarrage enregistrées dans les variables EFI, en plus d'un "
"chemin codé en dur, <filename>EFI/BOOT/BOOTX64.EFI</filename>. Normalement, "
"un chargeur d'amorçage devrait être installé dans un chemin personnalisé et "
"le chemin devrait être enregistré dans les variables EFI. L'utilisation du "
"chemin codé en dur est à éviter le plus possible. Cependant, dans certains "
"cas nous devons utiliser le chemin codé en dur&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:233
msgid ""
"The system is not booted with EFI yet, making EFI variables inaccessible."
msgstr ""
"Le système n'est pas encore démarré avec EFI, ce qui rend les variables EFI "
"inaccessibles."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:239
msgid ""
"The EFI firmware is 64-bit but the LFS system is 32-bit, making EFI "
"variables inaccessible because the kernel cannot invoke EFI runtime services"
" with a different virtual address length."
msgstr ""
"Le micrologiciel EFI est en 64&nbsp;bits mais le système LFS en "
"32&nbsp;bits, ce qui rend les variables EFI inaccessibles car le noyau ne "
"peut pas invoquer les services EFI à l'exécution avec une longueur "
"d'adressage virtuel différente."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:246
msgid ""
"LFS is built for a Live USB, so we cannot rely on EFI variables, which are "
"stored in NVRAM or EEPROM on the local machine."
msgstr ""
"LFS est construit pour une Live USB, donc nous ne pouvons pas nous reposer "
"sur les variables EFI qui sont stockées en NVRAM ou EEPROM sur la machine "
"locale."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:252
msgid ""
"You are unable or unwilling to install the "
"<application>efibootmgr</application> for manipulating boot entries in EFI "
"variables."
msgstr ""
"Vous ne pouvez pas ou ne voulez pas installer "
"<application>efibootmgr</application> pour manipuler les entrées de "
"démarrage dans les variables EFI."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:260
msgid ""
"In these cases, follow these instructions to install the GRUB EFI "
"application into the hardcoded path and make a minimal boot configuration. "
"Otherwise it's better to skip ahead and set up the boot configuration "
"normally."
msgstr ""
"Dans tous ces cas, suivez ces instructions pour installer l'application EFI "
"GRUB dans le chemin codé en dur et créer une configuration de démarrage "
"minimale. Sinon, il vaut mieux passer cette section et lire les sections "
"restantes pour paramétrer la configuration de démarrage normalement."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:267
msgid ""
"To install GRUB with the EFI application in the hardcoded path "
"<filename>EFI/BOOT/BOOTX64.EFI</filename>, first ensure the boot partition "
"is mounted at <filename class=\"directory\">/boot</filename> and the ESP is "
"mounted at <filename class=\"directory\">/boot/efi</filename>.  Then, as the"
" &root; user, run the command:"
msgstr ""
"Pour installer GRUB avec une application EFI installée dans le chemin codé "
"en dur <filename>EFI/BOOT/BOOTX64.EFI</filename>, assurez-vous d'abord que "
"la partition de démarrage est montée dans <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot</filename> et l'ESP est monté dans <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot/efi</filename>. Puis en tant qu'utilisateur "
"&root;, lancez la commande&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:277
msgid ""
"This command will overwrite "
"<filename>/boot/efi/EFI/BOOT/BOOTX64.EFI</filename>.  It may break a "
"bootloader already installed there.  Back it up if you are not sure."
msgstr ""
"La commande remplacera <filename>/boot/efi/EFI/BOOT/BOOTX64.EFI</filename>. "
"Elle peut casser un chargeur d'amorçage déjà installé. Sauvegardez-le si "
"vous n'êtes pas sur·e."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:283
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>grub-install --target=x86_64-efi --removable</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>grub-install --target=x86_64-efi --removable</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:286
msgid ""
"This command will install the GRUB EFI application into the hardcoded path "
"<filename>/boot/efi/EFI/BOOT/BOOTX64.EFI</filename>, so the EFI firmware can"
" find and load it.  The remaining GRUB files are installed in the <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot/grub</filename> directory and will be loaded by "
"<filename>BOOTX64.EFI</filename> during system boot."
msgstr ""
"Cette commande installera l'application EFI GRUB dans le chemin codé en dur "
"<filename>/boot/efi/EFI/BOOT/BOOTX64.EFI</filename>, pour que le "
"micrologiciel EFI puisse le trouver et le charger. Les fichiers GRUB "
"restants sont installés dans le répertoire <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot/grub</filename> et sera chargé par "
"<filename>BOOTX64.EFI</filename> au démarrage du système."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:295
msgid ""
"The EFI firmware usually prefers the EFI applications with a path stored in "
"EFI variables to the EFI application at the hardcoded path.  So you may need"
" to invoke the boot selection menu or firmware setting interface to select "
"the newly installed GRUB manually on the next boot.  Read the manual of your"
" motherboard or laptop to learn how."
msgstr ""
"Le micrologiciel EFI préfère les applications EFI avec le chemin enregistré "
"dans les entrées de démarrage stockées dans les variables EFI à "
"l'application EFI dans le chemin codé en dur. Vous devrez alors peut-être "
"invoquer le menu de sélection de démarrage ou l'interface de configuration "
"du micrologiciel pour choisir le GRUB nouvellement installé au prochain "
"démarrage. Consultez le manuel de votre carte mère ou de votre ordinateur "
"portable pour trouver comment."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:305
msgid ""
"If you've followed the instructions in this section and set up a minimal "
"boot configuration, now skip ahead to <quote>Creating the GRUB Configuration"
" File</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Si vous avez suivi les instructions de cette section et paramétrez une "
"configuration de démarrage minimale, sautez maintenant à <quote>Créer le "
"fichier de configuration GRUB</quote>."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:312
msgid "Mount the EFI Variable File System"
msgstr "Monter le système de fichiers des variables EFI"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:315
msgid ""
"The installation of GRUB on a UEFI platform requires that the EFI Variable "
"file system, <systemitem class=\"filesystem\">efivarfs</systemitem>, is "
"mounted.  As the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, "
"mount it if it's not already mounted:"
msgstr ""
"L'installation de GRUB sur une plateforme UEFI demande que le système de "
"fichiers des variables EFI, <systemitem "
"class=\"filesystem\">efivarfs</systemitem> soit monté. En tant "
"qu'utilisateur <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, montez-le "
"s'il n'est pas encore monté&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:321
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>mountpoint /sys/firmware/efi/efivars || mount -v -t efivarfs "
"efivarfs /sys/firmware/efi/efivars</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>mountpoint /sys/firmware/efi/efivars || mount -v -t efivarfs "
"efivarfs /sys/firmware/efi/efivars</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:325
msgid ""
"If the system is booted with UEFI and systemd, <systemitem "
"class=\"filesystem\">efivarfs</systemitem> will be mounted automatically.  "
"However, in the LFS chroot environment it still needs to be mounted "
"manually."
msgstr ""
"Si le système est démarré avec UEFI et systemd, <systemitem "
"class=\"filesystem\">efivarfs</systemitem> sera monté automatiquement. "
"Cependant dans l'environnement chroot de LFS il faudra toujours le monter "
"manuellement."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:333
msgid ""
"Now add an entry for the <systemitem "
"class=\"filesystem\">efivarfs</systemitem> in "
"<filename>/etc/fstab</filename> so it will be mounted automatically during "
"system boot:"
msgstr ""
"Maintenant ajoutez une entrée pour <systemitem "
"class=\"filesystem\">efivarfs</systemitem> dans "
"<filename>/etc/fstab</filename> pour qu'il soit monté automatiquement au "
"démarrage du système&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:339
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /etc/fstab &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal>efivarfs /sys/firmware/efi/efivars efivarfs defaults 0 0</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /etc/fstab &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal>efivarfs /sys/firmware/efi/efivars efivarfs defaults 0 0</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><warning><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:345
msgid ""
"If the system is not booted with UEFI, the directory <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/sys/firmware/efi</filename> will be missing. In this "
"case you should boot the system in UEFI mode with the emergency boot disk or"
" using a minimal boot configuration created as above, then mount <systemitem"
" class=\"filesystem\">efivarfs</systemitem> and continue."
msgstr ""
"Si le système n'est pas démarré avec UEFI, le répertoire <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/sys/firmware/efi</filename> n'existera pas. Dans ce cas"
" vous devriez démarrer le système en mode UEFI avec le disque de démarrage "
"d'urgence ou en utilisant la configuration de démarrage minimale créée plus "
"haut, puis monter <systemitem class=\"filesystem\">efivarfs</systemitem> et "
"continuer."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:356
msgid "Setting Up the Configuration"
msgstr "Mettre en place la configuration"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:359
msgid ""
"On UEFI based systems, GRUB works by installing an EFI application (a "
"special kind of executable) into <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot/efi/EFI/[id]/grubx64.efi</filename>, where "
"<filename class=\"directory\">/boot/efi</filename> is the mount point of the"
" ESP, and <literal>[id]</literal> is replaced with an identifier specified "
"in the <command>grub-install</command> command line.  GRUB will create an "
"entry in the EFI variables containing the path "
"<literal>EFI/[id]/grubx64.efi</literal> so the EFI firmware can find "
"<filename>grubx64.efi</filename> and load it."
msgstr ""
"Sur les systèmes UEFI, GRUB fonctionne en installant une application EFI (un"
" type d'exécutable spécial) dans <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot/efi/EFI/[id]/grubx64.efi</filename>, où <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot/efi</filename> est le point de montage de l'ESP et"
" <literal>[id]</literal> est remplacé par un identifiant spécifié à la ligne"
" de commande <command>grub-install</command>. GRUB créera une entrée dans "
"les variables EFI contenant le chemin "
"<literal>EFI/[id]/grubx64.efi</literal> pour que le micrologiciel puisse "
"trouver <filename>grubx64.efi</filename> et le charger."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:371
msgid ""
"<filename>grubx64.efi</filename> is very lightweight (136 KB with GRUB-2.06)"
" so it will not use much space in the ESP.  A typical ESP size is 100 MB "
"(for Windows boot manager, which uses about 50 MB in the ESP). Once "
"<filename>grubx64.efi</filename> has been loaded by the firmware, it will "
"load GRUB modules from the boot partition.  The default location is "
"<filename class=\"directory\">/boot/grub</filename>."
msgstr ""
"<filename>grubx64.efi</filename> est très léger (136&nbsp;Ko pour GRUB-2.06)"
" donc il n'utilisera pas beaucoup de place dans l'ESP. Une taille typique "
"d'ESP est 100&nbsp;Mo (pour le chargeur d'amorçage de Windows, qui prend "
"environ 50&nbsp;Mo dans l'ESP). Une fois <filename>grubx64.efi</filename> "
"chargé par le micrologiciel, il chargera les modules GRUB dans la partition "
"de démarrage. L'emplacement par défaut est <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot/grub</filename>."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:381
msgid ""
"As the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, install the "
"GRUB files into <filename>/boot/efi/EFI/LFS/grubx64.efi</filename> and "
"<filename class=\"directory\">/boot/grub</filename>. Then set up the boot "
"entry in the EFI variables:"
msgstr ""
"En tant qu'utilisateur <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, "
"installez les fichiers de GRUB dans "
"<filename>/boot/efi/EFI/LFS/grubx64.efi</filename> et <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot/grub</filename>. Ensuite paramétrez l'entrée de "
"démarrage dans les variables EFI&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:387
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>grub-install --bootloader-id=LFS --recheck</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>grub-install --bootloader-id=LFS --recheck</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:390
msgid "If the installation is successful, the output should be:"
msgstr ""
"Si l'installation se passe correctement, la sortie devrait être&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:393
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<literal>Installing for x86_64-efi platform.\n"
"Installation finished. No error reported.</literal>"
msgstr ""
"<literal>Installing for x86_64-efi platform.\n"
"Installation finished. No error reported.</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:397
msgid ""
"Issue the <command>efibootmgr | cut -f 1</command> command to recheck the "
"EFI boot configuration.  An example of the output is:"
msgstr ""
"Tapez <command>efibootmgr | cut -f 1</command> pour revérifier la "
"configuration de démarrage EFI. Voici un exemple de sortie&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:401
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<literal>BootCurrent: 0000\n"
"Timeout: 1 seconds\n"
"BootOrder: 0005,0000,0002,0001,0003,0004\n"
"Boot0000* ARCH\n"
"Boot0001* UEFI:CD/DVD Drive\n"
"Boot0002* Windows Boot Manager\n"
"Boot0003* UEFI:Removable Device\n"
"Boot0004* UEFI:Network Device\n"
"Boot0005* LFS</literal>"
msgstr ""
"<literal>BootCurrent: 0000\n"
"Timeout: 1 seconds\n"
"BootOrder: 0005,0000,0002,0001,0003,0004\n"
"Boot0000* ARCH\n"
"Boot0001* UEFI:CD/DVD Drive\n"
"Boot0002* Windows Boot Manager\n"
"Boot0003* UEFI:Removable Device\n"
"Boot0004* UEFI:Network Device\n"
"Boot0005* LFS</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:412
msgid ""
"Note that <literal>0005</literal> is the first in the "
"<literal>BootOrder</literal>, and <literal>Boot0005</literal> is "
"<literal>LFS</literal>. This means that on the next boot, the version of "
"GRUB installed by LFS will be used to boot the system."
msgstr ""
"Remarquez que <literal>0005</literal> est en premier dans "
"<literal>BootOrder</literal> et que <literal>Boot0005</literal> est "
"<literal>LFS</literal>. Cela signifie qu'au prochain démarrage, la version "
"de GRUB installée par LFS sera utilisée pour démarrer le système."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:421
msgid "Creating the GRUB Configuration File"
msgstr "Création du fichier de configuration de GRUB"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><indexterm><primary>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:424
msgid "/boot/grub/grub.cfg"
msgstr "/boot/grub/grub.cfg"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:428
msgid ""
"Generate <filename>/boot/grub/grub.cfg</filename> to configure the boot menu"
" of GRUB:"
msgstr ""
"Générez <filename>/boot/grub/grub.cfg</filename> pour configurer le menu de "
"démarrage de GRUB&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:432
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /boot/grub/grub.cfg &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal># Begin /boot/grub/grub.cfg\n"
"set default=0\n"
"set timeout=5\n"
"\n"
"insmod part_gpt\n"
"insmod ext2\n"
"set root=(hd0,2)\n"
"\n"
"insmod all_video\n"
"if loadfont /boot/grub/fonts/unicode.pf2; then\n"
"  terminal_output gfxterm\n"
"fi\n"
"\n"
"menuentry \"GNU/Linux, Linux 6.4.10-lfs-12.0\"  {\n"
"  linux   /boot/vmlinuz-6.4.10-lfs-12.0 root=/dev/sda2 ro\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"menuentry \"Firmware Setup\" {\n"
"  fwsetup\n"
"}</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /boot/grub/grub.cfg &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal># Begin /boot/grub/grub.cfg\n"
"set default=0\n"
"set timeout=5\n"
"\n"
"insmod part_gpt\n"
"insmod ext2\n"
"set root=(hd0,2)\n"
"\n"
"insmod all_video\n"
"if loadfont /boot/grub/fonts/unicode.pf2; then\n"
"  terminal_output gfxterm\n"
"fi\n"
"\n"
"menuentry \"GNU/Linux, Linux 6.4.10-lfs-12.0\"  {\n"
"  linux   /boot/vmlinuz-6.4.10-lfs-12.0 root=/dev/sda2 ro\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"menuentry \"Firmware Setup\" {\n"
"  fwsetup\n"
"}</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:456
msgid ""
"Refer to <ulink url='&lfs-root;/chapter10/grub.html'>the LFS book</ulink> "
"for the basic knowledge about the <filename>grub.cfg</filename> file.  "
"<literal>(hd0,2)</literal>, <literal>sda2</literal>, and "
"<literal>6.4.10-lfs-12.0</literal> must match your configuration."
msgstr ""
"Consultez <ulink url='&lfs-root;/chapter10/grub.html'>le livre LFS</ulink> "
"pour apprendre la base du fichier <filename>grub.cfg</filename>. Vous devez "
"remplacer <literal>(hd0,2)</literal>, <literal>sda2</literal> et "
"<literal>6.4.10-lfs-12.0</literal> pour correspondre à votre configuration."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:465
msgid ""
"The <command>insmod all_video</command> directive loads various modules for "
"video support.  It's needed to initialize the EFI framebuffer for the kernel"
" to print messages correctly before the kernel GPU driver initialization."
msgstr ""
"La directive <command>insmod all_video</command> charge plusieurs modules "
"pour la prise en charge vidéo. C'est requis pour initialiser le framebuffer "
"EFI pour que le noyau puisse afficher des messages correctement avant "
"l'initialisation du pilote GPU du noyau."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:472
msgid ""
"The <command>terminal_output gfxterm</command> directive changes the display"
" resolution of the GRUB menu to match your display device.  It will break "
"the rendering if the <filename>unicode.pf2</filename> font data file is not "
"loaded, so it's guarded by a <command>if</command> directive."
msgstr ""
"La directive <command>terminal_output gfxterm</command> change la résolution"
" de l'affichage du menu GRUB pour correspondre à votre écran. Elle cassera "
"le rendu si le fichier de données de polices "
"<filename>unicode.pf2</filename> n'est pas chargé, donc elle est encadrée "
"par une directive <command>if</command>."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:481
msgid ""
"From GRUB's perspective, the files are relative to the partitions used. If "
"you used a separate /boot partition, remove /boot from the above paths (to "
"kernel and to <filename>unicode.pf2</filename>). You will also need to "
"change the \"set root\" line to point to the boot partition."
msgstr ""
"Du point de vu de GRUB, les fichiers sont relatifs à la partition utilisée. "
"Si vous utilisez une partition /boot séparée, supprimez /boot dans les "
"chemins précédents (vers le noyau et vers <filename>unicode.pf2</filename>)."
" Vous devrez aussi changer la ligne «&nbsp;set root&nbsp;» pour pointer vers"
" la partition de démarrage."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:490
msgid ""
"The <literal>Firmware Setup</literal> entry can be used to enter the "
"configuration interface provided by the firmware (sometimes called "
"<quote>BIOS configuration</quote>)."
msgstr ""
"L'entrée <literal>Firmware Setup</literal> peut être utilisée pour entrer "
"dans l'interface de configuration fournie par le micrologiciel (parfois "
"nommée <quote>configuration BIOS</quote>)."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:497
msgid "Dual-booting with Windows"
msgstr "Démarrage double avec Windows"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:500
msgid "Add a menu entry for Windows into <filename>grub.cfg</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"Ajoutew une entrée de menu pour Windows dans "
"<filename>grub.cfg</filename>&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:503
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /boot/grub/grub.cfg &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal># Begin Windows addition\n"
"\n"
"menuentry \"Windows 11\" {\n"
"  insmod fat\n"
"  insmod chain\n"
"  set root=(hd0,1)\n"
"  chainloader /EFI/Microsoft/Boot/bootmgfw.efi\n"
"}</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /boot/grub/grub.cfg &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal># Begin Windows addition\n"
"\n"
"menuentry \"Windows 11\" {\n"
"  insmod fat\n"
"  insmod chain\n"
"  set root=(hd0,1)\n"
"  chainloader /EFI/Microsoft/Boot/bootmgfw.efi\n"
"}</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:515
msgid ""
"<literal>(hd0,1)</literal> should be replaced with the GRUB designated name "
"for the ESP.  The <literal>chainloader</literal> directive can be used to "
"tell GRUB to run another EFI executable, in this case the Windows Boot "
"Manager. You may put more usable tools in EFI executable format (for "
"example, an EFI shell) into the ESP and create GRUB entries for them, as "
"well."
msgstr ""
"Vous devriez remplacer <literal>(hd0,1)</literal> par le nom désigné par "
"GRUB pour l'ESP. Vous pouvez utiliser la directive "
"<literal>chainloader</literal> pour dire à GRUB de lancer un autre "
"exécutable EFI, dans ce cas le gestionnaire de démarrage de Windows. Vous "
"pouvez ajouter des outils supplémentaires au format exécutable EFI (par "
"exemple un shell EFI) dans l'ESP et leur créer des entrées GRUB."

#, no-wrap
#~ msgid ""
#~ "<userinput>mkdir -pv /mnt/rescue &amp;&amp;\n"
#~ "mount -v -t vfat /dev/sdx1 /mnt/rescue</userinput>"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "<userinput>mkdir -pv /mnt/rescue &amp;&amp;\n"
#~ "mount -v -t vfat /dev/sdx1 /mnt/rescue</userinput>"

